TopicTitle: 1.3 CTD with less than a half the mods I had in 1.2.2

Articles.Content: Make sure your running the 64bit executable had the same issue a while back steam updated me to the 32 bit version and I wondered why it kept crashing
KSP.exe is the 32 bit executable, use KSP_x64.exe. ALSO DON'T PUT THE LOG IN THE FORUM POST.

I'm running on x64 and I keep getting CTDs or freezes on loading. Sometimes, rather than sheer CTDs, it gets stuck forever on loading a particular asset, but the funny messages above keep changing, as in keep loading correctly. This is happening when trying to load more than 15+ mods.

I'm running on a:
1. AMD FX 8350 8 core processor, 4000 Mhz
2. Windows 7 (Service Pack 1) (64 bit)
3. 8GB RAM
4. AMD Radeon HD 7700 Series Graphic Card.

What's the best practise for sending logs? Thanks.

For uploading logs, put them on a file hosting site such as drop box or Google Drive then paste the link here. Also the error.log isn't as helpful as the out_put.log

The log there says you're running the 32 bit version of the game.

I just run on x64 a second time from the Steam selector and froze on me again. It got stuck on loading this time (for the record, ALL MY MODS are up-to-date), so it didn't throw me an error log.

Where can I get the out_put.log?

BTW, I've run a third time on x64 and I've just recovered from a BSOD (????). It NEVER happened before with any games I own whatsoever, and I've been having this rig for a good 3 years now. This is baffling honestly...

i suggest you start with a clean install and start it with the x64 exe then add 1 mod at a time till it goes pear shaped then remove it and add the others time consuming and a pain in the butt only way rto be sure
@VirtualgeniusI did a clean install and solved the mods issue, now I can run with a decen amount of those, thanks for the tip. I still get a BSOD every 10' tho. Do you know what may be causing it?
